-- Rogers in Talks to Purchase Maple Leafs, Raptors, Toronto Star Reports
-- B y   J o A n n e   N o r t o n
-- 2010-12-01T11:40:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-01/rogers-in-talks-to-buy-maple-leafs-raptors-for-1-3-billion-star-says.html
Rogers Communications Inc., Canada’s
largest wireless carrier, is in talks to buy the Toronto Maple
Leafs of professional hockey and Raptors basketball team for
about C$1.3 billion, the Toronto Star reported, citing people it
didn’t identify.  The purchase of the majority stake from the Ontario
Teachers’ Pension Plan would include the Toronto FC soccer club
and the Marlies, the Maple Leafs’ minor-league hockey team, as
well as media ventures, the Star reported. Rogers already owns
the Major League Baseball Toronto Blue Jays.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joanne Norton at 
 jnorton@bloomberg.net  